<article class='nx-article'>
  <header>
    <h1>2025-26 Bowl Season Second Half: Eight December Games That Matter</h1>
    <p class="nx-tagline">Holiday tradition meets underdog drama in the December 22-26 stretch of postseason football.</p>
  </header>
  <section class="nx-article__meta">
    <span class="nx-eyebrow">By Nexairi Sports · 10 min read</span>
  </section>
  <section class='nx-article__body'>
    <p>The bowl slate heats up post-Christmas with matchups blending holiday tradition, geographic rivalries, and Group of Five showdowns across Boise, Boca Raton, and beyond. These games deliver underdog energy and festive atmospheres before the New Year's majors. Casual fans will find plenty of intrigue in this December 22-26 stretch.</p>

    <h2>Famous Idaho Potato Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Toledo vs. Fresno State</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 22 (Monday) · 2:00 PM ET · Albertsons Stadium, Boise, ID</strong></p>
    <p>Toledo's MAC toughness meets Fresno State's West Coast flair in chilly Boise, where spud-themed celebrations add quirky charm to a potential shootout. Both squads feature dynamic quarterbacks promising highlight plays amid mountain air. A win catapults either into offseason spotlight. Debuting in 1997 to aid the Big West, the Famous Idaho Potato Bowl has grown into a Mountain West staple with memorable finishes like Northern Illinois' 2010 rout.</p>

    <h2>Boca Raton Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Northern Illinois vs. UTEP</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 23 (Tuesday) · 2:00 PM ET · Flagler Credit Union Stadium, Boca Raton, FL</strong></p>
    <p>Northern Illinois brings Mid-American grit against UTEP's desert resilience in sunny South Florida paradise. Beach proximity tempts players and fans alike for a relaxed yet competitive tussle. Expect opportunistic defenses forcing turnovers in humid conditions. Since 2014, the Boca Raton Bowl has showcased upsets like James Madison's 2024 victory, thriving on AAC-MAC battles in Florida Atlantic's home stadium.</p>

    <h2>New Orleans Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Louisiana Tech vs. Rice</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 23 (Tuesday) · 5:30 PM ET · Caesars Superdome, New Orleans, LA</strong></p>
    <p>Louisiana Tech's Bayou pride collides with Rice's academic-athletic balance inside the iconic Superdome amid Mardi Gras vibes. Creole cuisine and brass bands elevate this Sun Belt-AAC clash. Mobile quarterbacks could exploit soft secondaries for fireworks. Launched in 2001 with Colorado State's win over North Texas, the New Orleans Bowl consistently delivers close contests in New Orleans' football mecca.</p>

    <h2>Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>UNLV vs. Ohio</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 23 (Tuesday) · 9:00 PM ET · Ford Center at The Star, Frisco, TX</strong></p>
    <p>UNLV's Vegas flash meets Ohio's Bobcat tenacity at the Cowboys' training facility for a late-night prime time banger. Speedy offenses promise points in Frisco's modern venue. Coffee sponsorship fuels the high-energy atmosphere. Evolving from the Miami Beach Bowl, Scooter's Coffee Frisco Bowl since 2023 spotlights Group of Five contenders with ESPN broadcasts from Dallas suburbia.</p>

    <h2>Sheraton Hawai'i Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>San Jose State vs. South Alabama</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 24 (Wednesday) · 8:00 PM ET · Clarence T.C. Ching Athletics Complex, Honolulu, HI</strong></p>
    <p>Christmas Eve paradise football pits San Jose State's Mountain West speed against South Alabama's Jaguar toughness on Oahu's turf. Tropical setting rewards road teams with vacation incentives post-game. High-scoring history favors offensive fireworks. Created in 2002 after Hawaii's snub, the Sheraton Hawai'i Bowl boasts overtime thrillers and records like five-OT classics in its 20+ year run.</p>

    <h2>GameAbove Sports Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Central Michigan vs. Northwestern</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 26 (Friday) · 1:00 PM ET · Ford Field, Detroit, MI</strong></p>
    <p>Central Michigan's Chippewas battle Northwestern's Wildcats in Motown, blending MAC pride with Big Ten underdogs indoors. Lions-backed event offers NFL dome comfort during winter chill. Gritty defenses set up field position battle. Formerly Quick Lane Bowl since 2014, rebranded GameAbove Sports Bowl features MAC-Big Ten ties and six-OT marathons for postseason drama.</p>

    <h2>Rate Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>Kansas State vs. Rutgers</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 26 (Friday) · 4:30 PM ET · Chase Field, Phoenix, AZ</strong></p>
    <p>Big 12's Kansas State tangles with Big Ten's Rutgers in desert heat, where power running meets stubborn fronts. Roofed stadium ensures passing duels without weather excuses. Comeback lore adds intrigue to this hybrid conference tilt. Originating as Copper Bowl in 1989, evolved through Insight and Cheez-It eras, Rate Bowl holds FBS comeback records like Texas Tech's 2006 miracle.</p>

    <h2>SERVPRO First Responder Bowl</h2>
    <p><strong>UTSA vs. Marshall</strong></p>
    <p><strong>December 26 (Friday) · 8:00 PM ET · Gerald J. Ford Stadium, Dallas, TX</strong></p>
    <p>UTSA's Roadrunners soar against Marshall's Thundering Herd in Big D, honoring first responders with Texas-sized stakes. Conference USA showdown features explosive backs and home-run hitters. Nightcap slot builds prime time pressure. Since 2012 as Dallas Bowl, SERVPRO sponsorship highlights community heroes while delivering AAC-CUSA thrillers on SMU's field.</p>
  </section>
